# ============================================================
# SKILL CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: skill
scope: skill.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for skill.

## policy_rules
Skill policy constrains:
- who may view skill detail
- who may evaluate or update skill state
- how skill applicability may be disclosed
- when skill-based claims must be denied or escalated

## required_behavior
- evaluation scope must be explicit
- disclosure scope must be explicit
- applicability claims must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- bounded public skill summary
- holder-scoped detail
- evaluator/reviewer detail
- historical skill detail
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow skill evaluation only for valid scope
- allow skill disclosure only for allowed actors
- deny hidden authority widening through skill claims
- deny disclosure beyond allowed scope

## escalation_rules
If skill identity,
evaluation basis,
applicability scope,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the skill path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- evaluation policy is explicit
- disclosure matrix exists
- denial behavior is explicit
- escalation rules are explicit
